    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Thin, impervious material placed in construction to prevent water penetration and/or provide water drainage; generally located between a roof and a wall and over exterior door openings and windows.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000010761/Harris, Dictionary of Architecture and Construction (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dun, ondoordringbaar materiaal dat geplaatst wordt in bouwwerken om te voorkomen dat er water binnenkomt en/of om waterdrainage aan te brengen, over het algemeen geplaatst tussen dak en muur en boven buitendeuren en -ramen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
